6Mzk5NzY5MzMy"},"target":"37250a85c949e76cf1e9f9a35d6dcb2f164ffc98074326857a8623f756e50c6c","message":"As for the PRVHASH, this isn't a problem if `InitVec` specification is followed: it should be a uniformly-random sequence of bits, preferrably composed of 16-bit words with 4-12 bits set. It is impossible to obtain a 128-bit zero. `SeedXOR` on the other hand, can be any value - even if it is equal to the default Seed, the system won't break.","files":null}]}